articles.author: ROB GILLIES and FATIMA HUSSEIN
articles.description: WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. (AP) — Canadian Prime Minister Justin Trudeau flew to Florida on Friday to have dinner with President-elect Donald Trump at his Mar-a-Lago club after Trump threatened to impose sweeping tariffs on Canadian products.
articles.title: Canadian Prime Minister Trudeau flies to Florida to meet with Trump after tariffs threat

articles.author: CHRISTINE FERNANDO
articles.description: CHICAGO (AP) — In the days after the presidential election, Sadie Perez began carrying pepper spray with her around campus. Her mom also ordered her and her sister a self-defense kit that included keychain spikes, a hidden knife key and a personal alarm.
articles.title: Emboldened 'manosphere' accelerates threats and demeaning language toward women after US election

articles.author: SARAH EL DEEB
articles.description: BEIRUT (AP) — Thousands of Syrian insurgents fanned out inside Aleppo in vehicles with improvised armor and pickups, deploying to landmarks such as the old citadel on Saturday, a day after they entered Syria's largest city facing little resistance from government troops, according to residents and fighters.
articles.title: Syrian insurgents are inside Aleppo in a major setback for Assad as government forces regroup

articles.author: WAFAA SHURAFA, TIA GOLDENBERG and BASSEM MROUE
articles.description: DEIR AL-BALAH, Gaza Strip (AP) — An Israeli airstrike on a car in the Gaza Strip on Saturday killed five people, a senior Palestinian health official said.Three of them were said to be employees of the charity World Central Kitchen, whose aid delivery efforts in the war-ravaged territory were temporarily suspended earlier this year after an Israeli strike killed seven of its workers, most of them foreigners.
articles.title: Israeli strike in Gaza allegedly kills workers with World Central Kitchen charity

articles.author: BASSEM MROUE
articles.description: TYRE, Lebanon (AP) — The ceasefire between Israel and Hezbollah brought hope for normality back to many in southern Lebanon on Friday, including fishermen who long launched their wooden-hulled single-engine boats into the Mediterranean at dawn.
articles.title: Lebanese fisherman hope ceasefire with Israel means normal life returning

articles.author: MAURICIO SAVARESE and ELÉONORE HUGHES
articles.description: SAO PAULO (AP) — Brazil's Federal Police in late November formally accused far-right former President Jair Bolsonaro and 36 others of planning a coup to keep him in office.
articles.title: How Brazilian police say Bolsonaro plotted a coup to stay in office

articles.author: SOPHIKO MEGRELIDZE
articles.description: TBILISI, Georgia (AP) — More than 100 demonstrators were arrested overnight in Georgia as protesters clashed with police following the government’s decision to suspend negotiations to join the European Union, the country’s Interior Ministry said Saturday.
articles.title: More than 100 arrested as Georgian police clash with protesters over suspension of EU talks

articles.author: STEPHEN McGRATH
articles.description: BUCHAREST, Romania (AP) — Hundreds of protesters gathered in Bucharest after a far-right populist unexpectedly won the first round of a presidential race, plunging Romania into turmoil just days before the country holds parliamentary elections.
articles.title: Romania's parliamentary vote risks being overshadowed by presidential race chaos

articles.author: HYUNG-JIN KIM
articles.description: SEOUL, South Korea (AP) — North Korean leader Kim Jong Un vowed his country will “invariably support” Russia’s war in Ukraine as he met Russia's defense chief, the North’s state media reported Saturday.
articles.title: North Korea's Kim vows steadfast support for Russia’s war in Ukraine

articles.author: CAROLYN THOMPSON and ANTHONY IZAGUIRRE
articles.description: BUFFALO, N.Y. (AP) — The first big snowfall of the season is blanketing towns in upstate New York along lakes Erie and Ontario in the middle of the hectic holiday travel and shopping weekend, while numbing cold and heavy snow could persist into next week and cause hazards in the Great Lakes, Plains and Midwest regions.
articles.title: Great Lakes, Plains and Midwest forecast to be hit with snow and dangerous cold into next week
